es", "50g (1.7oz) Crushed Cornflakes"], "steps": ["Butterfly cut the chicken breast into thinner fillets. Season both sides with smoked paprika, onion powder, and garlic powder, rubbing the spices in well.", "In one bowl, add crushed cornflakes and season with the same spices used for the chicken. In a second bowl, crack in 2 eggs and whisk until smooth.", "Dip each chicken fillet into the egg wash, then coat thoroughly in the seasoned cornflakes. Place the coated chicken onto a baking tray (preferably with a wired rack).", "Bake in a preheated oven at 200°C (390°F) for 18–20 minutes or air fry at 180°C (360°F) for 18 minutes until golden and crispy.", "While the chicken cooks, toast the brioche buns and prep your toppings: lettuce, tomato, pickles, light cheese, and special sauce.", "Assemble the burger: spread the sauce on the buns, layer with lettuce, tomato, crispy chicken, cheese, and pickles. Serve & ENJOY! Return to Table of Contents 36"], "canonical_ingredients": ["chicken_breast", "corn", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "lettuce", "mayo", "mustard", "onion", "onion_powder", "paprika", "sriracha", "tomato"], "tags": ["asian"], "cook_min": 42, "prep_min": 13, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["beef", "chicken"]}, {"id": "jalal_buffalo_chicken_mac_cheese", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 37, "name": "Buffalo Chicken Mac & Cheese", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 532, "protein": 63.0, "carbs": 51.0, "fat": 9.0}, "ingredients": ["150g (5.3oz) Low Fat Cottage Cheese", "1 Chicken Breast", "110g (3.8oz) Uncooked", "200g (7.1oz) Light Cream Cheese Cut Into Halves Macaroni (For 2 Servings)", "30g (1.1oz) Lower Fat Cheddar Cheese", "1 Tsp Paprika", "1 Tsp Salt", "50ml (1.7oz) Low Fat/Skimmed Milk", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder", "Boiling Water", "1 Tsp Garlic", "1 Tsp Onion Powder", "75g (2.7oz) Buffalo Sauce", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "1 Tsp Olive Oil"], "steps": ["Slice the chicken breast into 2 thinner fillets, then season both sides with papri