easonings along with You may need to add a little Greek yogurt (or any yogurt you prefer). Mix well until the color changes, water or tomato sauce to add then marinate overnight for the best flavor. more sauce.", "In a pot, add washed uncooked basmati rice, water, turmeric, cumin, and salt. Bring to a gentle boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook until the rice is fluffy and fully cooked.", "Heat a pan on medium, cook the chicken for 4 minutes on each side until golden, then set aside.", "In the same pan, add chopped onion with more seasoning and cook for 2 minutes. Then add tomato sauce or canned tomatoes along with light cream cheese, stirring well. Return the chicken to the pan.", "Mix everything together and let it simmer for 2-3 minutes. Garnish with coriander, serve with the yellow rice, and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 50"], "canonical_ingredients": ["chili_powder", "coconut_milk", "cream_cheese", "cumin", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "milk", "onion", "paprika", "pepper", "salt", "tomato", "yogurt"], "tags": ["indian"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 13, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["chicken"]}, {"id": "jalal_sweet_and_sour_chicken", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 51, "name": "Sweet and Sour Chicken", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 434, "protein": 50.0, "carbs": 49.0, "fat": 4.0}, "ingredients": ["300g (10.6oz) Chicken Breast, cubed", "30g (1.1oz) Ketchup (Can Use", "1 Onion, Finely Chopped", "1 Tbsp Garlic Powder Reduced", "Add 1/2 Tsp of the Same", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper Sugar Version) Seasonings Used for Chicken", "2-3 Tbsp Light Soy Sauce", "2 Tbsp Light Soy Sauce", "250g (8.8oz) Crushed", "1 Tbsp Light Brown Sugar Tomatoes (Passata)", "15g Corn Flour (Makes it Crispy)", "1 Tbsp Rice Vinegar (Optional)", "80-100g (3.5oz) Light Cream", "1 Tsp Corn Flour (To Cheese Thicken the Sauce) (You Can Use Yogurt or Coconut Milk Instead|)", "1/2 Cup Water", "Serve with 140g (5oz) of Cooked Rice per Serving"], "steps": ["Slice the chicken into bite-sized pieces, then season with garlic powder, salt, black pepper, soy sauce, and corn flour. Mix well until all pieces are evenly coated. Chop your vegetables into square pieces and set aside.", "In a separate bowl, combine ketchup (preferably low sugar), light soy sauce, light brown sugar, rice vinegar, corn flour, and water. Stir until the mixture is smooth and the sugar has fully dissolved.", "Heat a pan on high with cooking spray or olive oil, then cook the chicken for about 8 minutes (4 minutes per side) until golden and crispy. Remove the chicken and set aside.", "In the same pan, add chopped onions and bell peppers. Cook for 4 minutes until slightly soft, then pour in the sauce and let it simmer until it thickens.", "Add the cooked chicken back into the pan, mix everything together until well coated, then garnish with green onion and sesame seeds. Serve with rice and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 51"], "canonical_ingredients": ["brown_sugar", "chicken_breast", "corn", "cornstarch", "flour", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "ketchup", "onion", "pepper", "salt", "soy_sauce", "sugar", "tomato", "vinegar"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean", "indian"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 13, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["chicken"]}, {"id": "jalal_bbq_chicken_tenders", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 52, "name": "BBQ Chicken Tenders", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 227, "protein": 32.0, "carbs": 22.0, "fat": 1.0}, "ingredients": ["400g (14.1oz) of Chicken", "80g (2.8oz) Crushed Cornflake", "30ml (1.1oz) BBQ Sauce Breast Cut Into Strips", "1 Tsp Paprika", "1/2 Lime Juice", "60ml (2.1oz) Sugar", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder Free BBQ Sauce", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "2 Tsp Black Pepper", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder"], "steps": ["Cut the chicken into strips and place them in a bowl. Add BBQ sauce, black pepper, garlic powder, and paprika. Mix well until all the strips are fully coated in the marinade.", "In a separate bowl, mix c