nder, garlic powder, till desired consistency and you salt, pepper, lime juice, and a little water. Blend until smooth and creamy. will only use a small amount per", "In a pot, add water and washed basmati rice along with the same seasonings serving. used for the chicken and 1–2 tbsp of tomato paste. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 8–10 minutes until cooked.", "Heat a pan on high, spray with oil, and cook the chicken for 3–4 minutes on each side until golden brown. Remove and set aside. In the same pan, cook the chopped peppers and onions for 5 minutes until soft.", "Serve with the tomato rice, cooked chicken, sautéed veggies, shredded lettuce, black beans, sweet corn, lime, sour cream or yogurt, and a generous drizzle of the green sauce. Return to Table of Contents 56"], "canonical_ingredients": ["avocado", "bell_pepper", "black_beans", "chicken_breast", "chili_flakes", "cilantro", "cooking_spray", "corn", "cumin", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "lettuce", "olive_oil", "onion", "oregano", "paprika", "salt", "sour_cream", "tomato", "tomato_paste", "yogurt"], "tags": ["mexican", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 18, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["chicken"]}, {"id": "jalal_high_protein_shawarma", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 57, "name": "High Protein Shawarma", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 390, "protein": 45.0, "carbs": 35.0, "fat": 7.0}, "ingredients": ["250g (8.8oz) of Raw Chicken", "400g (14.1oz) Uncooked Potato Cut", "1 Wholemeal Pita Wrap / Flatbread Breast Cut Into Strips Into Fries (You Will Only Use", "2 Tbsp Garlic sauce", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder 50g, (17oz) Cooked per Wrap)", "Chicken Pieces", "1 Tsp Paprika", "1 Tsp Cornstarch", "50g (1.7oz) of Cooked Fries", "1 Tsp Turmeric", "Pickles", "1 Tsp Cumin", "1 Tsp Black Pepper", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "1 Tsp Salt (At the End After Cooking) Quick tip:", "2 Tbsp Tomato Paste Garlic sauce:", "You can toast the wrap in a pan", "1/2 Lemon Juice", "3 Tbsp Fat Free Greek Yogurt to make it a little crispy and firm", "2 Tbsp Low Fat Mayo", "1/2 Tsp Garlic Powder", "1/2 Tsp Salt"], "steps": ["Cut the chicken into strips and season with all the listed spices, tomato paste, and lemon juice. Mix thoroughly to coat the chicken evenly and set aside to marinate.", "Preheat the oven to 220°C (430°F). Slice the potato into fries, then toss with cornstarch, paprika, black pepper, and a light spray of cooking oil. Spread the fries out on a lined baking tray and bake for 20 minutes, turning halfway through if needed.", "While the fries are in the oven, heat a pan over medium heat, spray with oil, and cook the marinated chicken for 3–4 minutes on each side until golden brown and cooked through. Avoid overcooking to keep the chicken tender.", "In a small bowl, mix together all the ingredients for the garlic sauce until smooth and creamy. Adjust seasoning to taste if needed.", "To assemble, take a flatbread and spread a generous layer of garlic sauce. Add a few pieces of cooked chicken, about 50g of fries, and some sliced pickle. Drizzle with more garlic sauce on top, wrap or fold, and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 57"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bread", "corn", "cornstarch", "cumin", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "mayo", "paprika", "pepper", "potato", "salt", "tomato", "tomato_paste", "wrap", "yogurt"], "tags": ["mediterranean", "indian"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 16, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_bbq_chicken_pizza", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 58, "name": "BBQ Chicken Pizza", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 418, "protein": 56.0, "carbs": 31.0, "fat": 9.0}, "ingredients": ["140g (5oz) Raw Chicken Breast (Seasoned with Sauce: Salt, Pepper, Paprika and Garlic Powder)", "430g (15.1oz) Sugar Free BBQ Sauce", "1 Lebanese Flatbread", "20g (1oz) Frank’s Red Hot Sauce", "Thin Layer of BBQ sauce (or Any Hot Sauce You Like)", "30g (1.1oz) Low Fat Mozzarella", "1 Red Onion", "Garnish with Spring Onion", "Extra BBQ Sauce (Optional)"], "steps": ["Preheat the oven to 180°C (350°F) and place the Lebanese flatbread on a baking tray. In a bowl, mix BBQ sauce with hot sauce and spread a thin, even layer over the flatbread.", "Season the chicken breast to your preference, cook in a pan for about 5 minutes on each side until fully cooked, then remove and let it rest for a few minutes. Shred the chicken using two forks and mix it with the remaining BBQ sauce.", "Top the flatbread with low-fat mozzarella, the shredded BBQ chicken, and thinly sliced red onion.", "Bake in the preheated oven for about 7 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and everything is heated through.", "Once out of the oven, drizzle with extra BBQ sauce, garnish with chopped spring onion, and enjoy hot! Return to Table of Contents 58"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bbq_sauce", "bread", "cheese_mozzarella", "chicken_breast", "green_onion", "hot_sauce", "onion", "sugar", "wrap"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["chicken"]}, {"id": "jalal_delicious_chicken_stir_fry", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 59, "name": "Delicious Chicken Stir Fry", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 418, "protein": 56.0, "carbs": 38.0, "fat": 7.0}, "ingredients": ["300g (10.6oz) Raw Chicken Breast, cut into cubes Stir fry:", "1 Heaping Tsp Paprika", "2 Tsp Olive Oil", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder", "1 Medium Onion, Finely Chopped", "1 Tsp Black Pepper", "1 Medium Red Bell Pepper, Chopped", "1.5 Tbsp Soy Sauce", "1 Tsp Each of Paprika, Garlic Powder (I Used Dark But You Can Use Light) & Pepper (For Seasoning)", "1 Tbsp Soy Sauce", "1 Cup Broccoli", "200g (7.1oz) Cooked Basmati Rice", "Sprinkle Sesame Seeds (Optional)"], "steps": ["Season the chicken with paprika, garlic powder, black pepper, and soy sauce. Mix well until the chicken is evenly coated and its color changes slightly.", "Chop all the vegetables, then heat a pan over mediu