 the Beef Really Tender!)", "1 Tbsp Cornstarch", "1 Tsp White Pepper or Black Pepper"], "steps": ["Slice the steak into thin strips, ideally cutting on a diagonal for tenderness. Marinate the beef with olive oil, soy sauce, rice vinegar, baking soda, cornstarch, and white pepper. Mix well and let it sit while you prepare the other ingredients.", "Chop your vegetables, then prepare the stir-fry sauce in a bowl by mixing soy sauce, oyster sauce, rice vinegar, water, and cornstarch until smooth.", "Heat a pan on high and spray with oil. Add the marinated beef in batches, cooking 1–2 minutes per side until browned. Avoid overcrowding the pan. Remove and set aside.", "In the same pan, add a small amount of olive oil, followed by garlic, ginger, red chilli, and green onion. Stir- fry for 2–3 minutes until fragrant, then pour in the prepared sauce. Let it cook for another minute or so until it thickens.", "Return the beef to the pan, toss everything together until well coated, and serve with hot jasmine rice. Garnish with sesame seeds and extra green onion, then enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 86"], "canonical_ingredients": ["cooking_spray", "corn", "cornstarch", "ginger", "green_onion", "ketchup", "olive_oil", "onion", "pepper", "soy_sauce", "steak", "sugar", "vinegar"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 14, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["beef"]}, {"id": "jalal_steak_stir_fry", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 87, "name": "Steak Stir Fry", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 290, "protein": 39.0, "carbs": 17.0, "fat": 9.0}, "ingredients": ["200g (7.1oz) Lean Beef Steak, cut into thin strips", "2 Tbsp Worcestershire Sauce", "1 Carrot, Diced", "1 Tsp Pepper", "100g (3.5oz) Broccoli", "1 Tbsp Garlic Powder or Fresh Garlic, Chopped", "1 Red Bell Pepper", "1 Tbsp Ginger Powder or Fresh Ginger, Crushed", "Handful of Cashew Nuts", "1 Tsp Olive Oil or Cooking", "2 Tbsp Soy Sauce (Low Sodium)"], "steps": ["Slice t