n over high heat. Add a small piece of butter, then place the meatballs in the pan. Use a spatula to smash them into patties and add sliced onion to the pan beside them. Cook for about 2 minutes, then flip everything.", "Lower the heat, place a slice of cheese on one of the patties, and stack the other patty on top. Toast your burger buns in the same pan until golden.", "Mix mustard, sriracha, and light mayo in a bowl to make the sauce. Spread the sauce generously on both sides of the buns.", "Assemble the burger in this order: lettuce, the double-stacked patties, tomato slice, grilled onion, and gherkin slices. Serve and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 88"], "canonical_ingredients": ["lettuce", "mayo", "mustard", "onion", "salt", "sriracha", "tomato"], "tags": ["asian"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["beef"]}, {"id": "jalal_high_protein_kebab", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 89, "name": "High Protein Kebab", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 405, "protein": 39.0, "carbs": 36.0, "fat": 10.0}, "ingredients": ["300g (10.6oz) Ground Beef/", "100g (3.5oz) Low Fat", "2 Wholemeal Flatbread Wraps Mince (Raw Weight) Greek Yogurt", "White Sauce", "3 Garlic Cloves, Minced", "1 Tsp Salt and Pepper", "Shredded Lettuce", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder", "Red Onion", "2 Tsp Cumin", "1/2 or 1 Lemon Juice", "Tomato Slices", "2 Tsp Smoked Paprika", "1 Tbsp Coriander or", "3 Kebabs (per Wrap)", "1 Tbsp Fresh Coriander Mint, Chopped", "Sriracha"], "steps": ["In a bowl combine ground beef with minced garlic, your preferred spices, and chopped coriander. Mix thoroughly until everything is well incorporated.", "Place the mixture in the fridge for about 10 minutes to help the meat firm up and hold its shape better.", "Shape the meat into kebab-style pieces and bake in a preheated oven for around 10 minutes. Be careful not to overcook them, as they can dry out.", "While the kebabs are cooking, prepare yo