on Juice Sriracha & Lemon Juice)", "Green Onion & Sesame Seeds (For Garnish)"], "steps": ["Slice your skinless salmon into bite-sized cubes. Add your seasonings, garlic powder, paprika or chilli flakes, soy sauce, and a touch of oil—then mix until the salmon is evenly coated. Set aside while you prepare the rest.", "Thinly slice your red onion and carrot, then make a quick cucumber salad by combining sliced cucumber with soy sauce, garlic powder, chilli flakes or paprika, and a splash of rice vinegar. Stir well and let it sit to marinate.", "Rinse your jasmine rice thoroughly, then cook it in boiling water until fluffy. While the rice cooks, heat a pan on medium heat with a bit of oil and sear the salmon cubes for 2–3 minutes on each side until golden and slightly crisp on the edges.", "Prepare your toppings: slice avocado, and if using, mix up a spicy lemon mayo by combining light mayo with a bit of hot sauce and lemon juice.", "Assemble your bowl with a portion of rice, cooked salmon, cucumber salad, sliced onion, carrot, and avocado. Drizzle over the spicy lemon mayo and top with sesame seeds and chopped green onion if you like. Serve and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 93"], "canonical_ingredients": ["avocado", "carrot", "chili_flakes", "cucumber", "garlic", "green_onion", "honey", "lemon", "mayo", "onion", "paprika", "rice_white", "salmon", "sesame_seeds", "soy_sauce", "sriracha", "vinegar"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 14, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["seafood"]}, {"id": "jalal_honey_garlic_shrimp_stir_fry", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 94, "name": "Honey Garlic Shrimp Stir Fry", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 436, "protein": 46.0, "carbs": 54.0, "fat": 4.0}, "ingredients": ["450-500g (17.6oz) Shrimp (Raw or Pre-Cooked)", "1-2 Tsp Olive Oil or Cooking Spray", "4 Garlic Cloves, Minced", "1 Red Onion, Sliced Thinly", "1 Tsp Smoked Paprika", "1/2 Red Bell Pepper, Sliced", "1 Tsp Black Pepper", "1/2 Yellow Bell Pepper, Sliced", "1/2 or 1 Tsp Chilli Flakes", "100g (3.5oz) Broccoli", "1 Tbsp Honey", "1-2 Garlic Cloves, Minced", "1/2 Lemon Juice (Or Lime)", "1 Tbsp Dark & Light Soy Sauce", "1 Tbsp Dark Soy Sauce", "240g (8.4oz) Cooked Basmati Rice", "Sesame Seeds (For Garnish)"], "steps": ["Season the shrimp with minced garlic, smoked paprika, pepper, chilli flakes, honey, lemon juice, and soy sauce. Mix until everything is well combined, then set aside to marinate.", "Thinly slice the onion, bell peppers, and broccoli. Heat a pan on medium heat with a little olive oil, then cook the shrimp for about 2 minutes on each side until golden and pink. Remove and set aside.", "In the same pan, add the sliced vegetables and cook for 3–4 minutes until they begin to soften.", "Push the veggies to the side and add a bit more garlic, honey, and soy sauce in the middle. Let it bubble and caramelise for a minute, then mix everything together.", "Add cooked basmati rice (about one portion) and stir to combine well. Return the shrimp to the pan, toss everything together, sprinkle sesame seeds on top and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 94"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bell_pepper", "broccoli", "chili_flakes", "cooking_spray", "honey", "olive_oil", "onion", "paprika", "pepper", "sesame_seeds", "shrimp", "soy_sauce"], "tags": ["asian", "mexican", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 13, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["seafood"]}, {"id": "jalal_creamy_shrimp_pasta", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 95, "name": "Creamy Shrimp Pasta", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 490, "protein": 55.0, "carbs": 45.0, "fat": 10.0}, "ingredients": ["400g (14.1oz) Shrimp", "150-180ml (6.3oz) Low Fat Milk", "1 Tsp Salt (Fresh or Frozen)", "100g (3.5oz) Light Cream Cheese", "120-130g (4.6oz) Uncooked", "4 Garlic Cloves, Minced", "20g (1oz) Grated Parmesan Linguine (or Any Pasta of Choice)", "1 Tbsp Italian Herbs", "1/2 Tsp Italian Herbs", "1 Tsp Paprika", "1/2 Tsp Garlic Powder", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "30ml (1.1oz) Pasta Water", "1/2 Tsp Chilli Flakes", "Handful of Spinach", "1/2 Lemon Juice", "Cook in 1-2 Tsp Olive Oil or Cooking Spray"], "steps": ["Rinse and pat dry the shrimp, then place in a bowl. Add minced fresh garlic, Italian herbs, paprika, salt, pepper, chilli flakes, and a splash of lemon juice. Mix until the shrimp are evenly coated, then set aside to marinate briefly.", "Heat a pan over medium heat and add olive oil or cooking spray. Once hot, add the shrimp and cook for 3–4 minutes, flipping halfway, until golden and fully cooked. Remove from the pan and set aside.", "Reduce the heat to low. In the same pan, pour in a bit of milk and add cream cheese, grated parmesan, Italian herbs, garlic powder, and a splash of reserved pasta water. Stir continuously until the mixture melts and forms a smooth, creamy sauce.", "Add a handful of fresh spinach, then return the cooked shrimp to the pan along with your pre-cooked pasta. Toss everything together until well combined and the spinach wilts.", "Once the dish is evenly heated and coated in the sauce, serve immediately. Optionally garnish with extra parmesan or herbs. Return to Table of Contents 95"], "canonical_ingredients": ["cheese_parmesan", "chili_flakes", "cooking_spray", "cream_cheese", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "italian_seasoning", "milk", "olive_oil", "paprika", "salt", "shrimp", "spinach"], "tags": ["mediterranean", "italian"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 13, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["seafood"]}, {"id": "jalal_creamy_salmon_pasta", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 96, "name": "Creamy Salmon Pasta", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 640, "protein": 57.0, "carbs": 42.0, "fat": 25.0}, "ingredients": ["480g (16.9oz) Salmon", "1-2 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "2 cups Wholewheat Pasta", "1 Tbsp Italian Herbs", "4 Garlic Cloves, Minced", "2 Tbsp Low Fat Cream Cheese", "Handful of Sun Dried Tomatoes", "1/2 Cup Milk of Choice", "1 Onion, Chopped"], "steps": ["Fill a large pot with water and bring it to a boil. Add salt, then stir in the pasta. Cook for 8–10 minutes until al dente. Before draining, reserve about ½ cup of pasta water. Drain the pasta and set aside.", "In a hot pan, lightly spray with oil and add garlic cloves, sun-dried tomatoes, and chopped onion. Season with salt, pepper, and Italian herbs. Sauté for about 5 minutes until the onions are soft and fragrant.", "Transfer the sautéed mixture to a blender. Add the reserved pasta water, cream cheese, and a splash of almond or low-fat milk. Blend for 1–2 minutes until smooth and creamy.", "Season salmon fillets with salt and pepper. Heat a pan over medium-high heat with a little oil or spray. Cook the salmon for about 6 minutes per side until golden and cooked through. Set aside.", "Lower the heat and return the pasta to the pan. Pour in the sauce and stir to coat evenly. Place the salmon on top, cover briefly to warm everything through, then serve immediately. Return to Table of Contents 96"], "canonical_ingredients": ["cream_cheese", "italian_seasoning", "milk", "onion", "salmon", "salt", "tomato"], "tags": ["italian"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["seafood"]}, {"id": "jalal_honey_salmon_rice", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 97, "name": "Honey Salmon & Rice", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 615, "protein": 57.0, "carbs": 46.0, "fat": 20.0}, "ingredients": ["500g (17.6oz) Salmon Fillet (250g", "Broccoli & Asparagus (8.8oz) per Serving)", "Season With Salt & Pepper, Garlic", "1 Tbsp Dijon Mustard Powder & Lemon juice", "4 Garlic Cloves, Crushed", "Serve With 100-120g (4.2oz) of", "1/2 Lemon Juice Cooked Jasmine Rice", "1 Tsp Paprika,", "1 Tsp Dried Parsley", "1/2 Tsp Chilli Flakes,", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "1 Tsp Honey"], "steps": ["In a bowl, combine all the marinade ingredients and mix thoroughly If you use skinless salmon the until smooth and well blended. calories will be lower!", "Preheat your oven to 220°C (430°F). Line a baking tray with parchment paper and place the salmon fillets on top. Spoon the marinade evenly over each piece, spreading it to coat fully.", "Switch your oven setting to broil. Place the salmon in the oven and broil for 6–10 minutes, depending on thickness. Keep an eye on it to avoid overcooking.", "While the salmon cooks, stir-fry your choice of vegetables in a hot pan, or roast them alongside the salmon in the oven if you prefer.", "Once everything is ready, plate the salmon with your veggies and a portion of jasmine rice. Serve immediately and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 97"], "canonical_ingredients": ["broccoli", "chili_flakes", "garlic", "honey", "lemon", "mustard", "paprika", "parsley", "rice_white", "salmon", "salt"], "tags": ["mediterranean"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 11, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["seafood"]}, {"id": "jalal_tuna_stir_fry", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 98, "name": "Tuna Stir Fry", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 325, "protein": 34.0, "carbs": 35.0, "fat": 6.0}, "ingredients": ["1 Tsp Olive Oil", "2 Cans of Tuna (110g (3.8oz)", "1 Red Onion, Thinly Diced Drained Weight per Can)", "1 Bell Pepper, Chopped (Red and Yellow)", "1 Cup of Cooked Rice (Can easily adjust this depending on your calorie goals)", "Handful of Broccoli", "1/2 Tsp Chilli Flakes", "1 Tbsp Soy Sauce", "1 Tsp Dried Parsley", "1 Tbsp Oyster Sauce", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder", "Sesame Seeds & Spring Onion, for Garnish (Optional)", "1 Tsp Gaprika"], "steps": ["Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and add a small amount of olive oil. Once hot, add your chopped vegetables (like bell peppers, carrots, or onions) along with your spices of choice — garlic powder, black pepper, and a pinch of chili flakes work great. Sauté everything for about 2 minutes until the veggies start to soften.", "Add in the canned tuna and stir it through the veggies, letting it cook for another 2 minutes to warm up and absorb the flavors.", "Next, add your cooked rice followed by soy sauce and oyster sauce. Mix everything together thoroughly to coat the rice and tuna in the sauces. Let it cook for another 2 minutes so the flavors blend well.", "Finish by sprinkling over some sesame seeds and freshly chopped spring onion. Serve warm and enjoy your quick and flavorful tuna fried rice! Return to Table of Contents 98"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bell_pepper", "broccoli", "chili_flakes", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "green_onion", "olive_oil", "onion", "parsley", "sesame_seeds", "soy_sauce", "tuna"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 11, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["seafood"]}, {"id": "jalal_fresh_salmon_bowl", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 99, "name": "Fresh Salmon Bowl", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 800, "protein": 60.0, "carbs": 67.0, "fat": 24.0}, "ingredients": ["240g (8.4oz) 2 Salmon Fillets Dressing/Marinade:", "1 Cup Cooked Jasmine Rice", "1 Tbsp Soya Sauce", "1 Carrot, Peeled", "1 Tbsp Sriracha", "1/2 Red Bell Pepper, Sliced", "1 Lime, Juiced", "Handful Edamame Beans", "1/2 Apple, Thinly Diced", "1/2 Avocado, Sliced", "Spring Onion and Sesame Seeds, for Garnish"], "steps": ["Cut the salmon into bite-sized cubes and prepare your marinade by Use skinless salmon for less fat mixing your preferred ingredients. Coat the salmon evenly with the and you can add or replace with marinade and let it sit briefly to absorb the flavors. any veg or fruit you’d prefer!", "Heat a pan over medium heat and add a little oil or cooking spray. Cook the salmon cubes for about 2 minutes on each side until golden and just cooked through. Set aside.", "In a large serving bowl, start by adding your cooked rice as the base.", "Arrange the cooked salmon along with the avocado, cucumber, edamame, mango, and carrots, and place evenly around the rice.", "Drizzle some extra dressing over the top and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Serve immediately and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 99"], "canonical_ingredients": ["apple", "avocado", "bell_pepper", "carrot", "green_onion", "onion", "rice_white", "salmon", "sesame_seeds", "sriracha"], "tags": ["asian", "mexican"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["seafood"]}, {"id": "jalal_tuna_pasta_bake", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 100, "name": "Tuna Pasta Bake", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 340, "protein": 40.0, "carbs": 30.0, "fat": 6.0}, "ingredients": ["100g (3.5oz) Uncooked Pasta", "Handful Grated Mozzarella", "1-2 Tuna Cans", "1 Tsp Mixed Italian Herbs", "1 Bell Pepper, diced", "1/2 Tsp Red Chilli Flakes", "1 Onion, diced", "1 Tsp salt", "3-4 Garlic Cloves, finely chopped", "1 Tsp Pepper", "1 Can Chopped Tomatoes", "1 Tsp Olive Oil or Cooking Spray"], "steps": ["Cook the pasta according to the package instructions. While it’s cooking, dice the onion and bell pepper, and finely chop the garlic.", "In a pan, heat a bit of olive oil over medium heat. Add the onion, garlic, bell pepper, and chopped tomatoes. Season with salt, pepper, Italian herbs, and chilli flakes.", "Stir and cook for about 5 minutes until the vegetables soften. Stir in the tuna and the cooked pasta. Mix everything well, then transfer to a baking dish.", "Top with shredded mozzarella and bake in a preheated oven at 180ºC for 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and serve hot—enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 100"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bell_pepper", "cheese_mozzarella", "chili_flakes", "cooking_spray", "italian_seasoning", "olive_oil", "onion", "salt", "tomato", "tuna"], "tags": ["mediterranean", "italian"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 11, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["seafood"]}, {"id": "jalal_fresh_shrimp_salad", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 101, "name": "Fresh Shrimp Salad", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 425, "protein": 50.0, "carbs": 28.0, "fat": 12.0}, "ingredients": ["250g (8.8oz) Jumbo/Red Shrimps", "1 Handful Blueberries", "(one pack raw weight)", "1/2 Avocado", "1 Tsp Salt Dressing:", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder", "1 Tsp Paprika", "1 Tbsp Honey Mustard", "1 Pinch Chilli Flakes", "1/2 Tsp Salt", "1/2 Lemon Juice", "1/2 Tsp Black Pepper", "Mixed Salad Greens (your choice of salad)", "1/2 Tsp Garlic Powder", "100g (3.5oz) Cherry Tomatoes", "Lemon Juice", "1/2 Red Onion"], "steps": ["Add the shrimp to a mixing bowl and season with salt, garlic powder, paprika, chilli flakes, and freshly squeezed lemon juice. Toss thoroughly so the seasoning coats each piece evenly. Set aside to briefly marinate while you prep the rest.", "Slice the cherry tomatoes in halves, thinly slice the red onion, and cube or slice the avocado. In a large salad bowl, add a base of fresh salad greens, then top with the prepared tomatoes, onion, avocado, and a handful of blueberries.", "For the dressing (optional but recommended), whisk together honey mustard, a pinch of salt and pepper, garlic powder, and a bit more lemon juice until well combined and creamy.", "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and cook the marinated shrimp for 2–3 minutes on each side until golden and cooked through. Add the shrimp to the salad, drizzle generously with the dressing, and serve immediately—fresh, zesty, and full of flavour! Return to Table of Contents 101"], "canonical_ingredients": ["avocado", "blueberry", "cherry_tomato", "chili_flakes", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "honey", "lemon", "mustard", "onion", "paprika", "pepper", "salt", "shrimp", "tomato"], "tags": ["mediterranean"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 13, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["seafood"]}, {"id": "jalal_garlic_parmesan_fries", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 102, "name": "Garlic Parmesan Fries", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 356, "protein": 53.0, "carbs": 14.0, "fat": 9.0}, "ingredients": ["250g (8.8oz) Raw Potato,", "Cooking Spray The sauce: cut into thin fries", "1 Tbsp Light Mayo Garnish with:", "1 Tbsp Garlic Powder", "1-2 Tbsp Fat Free Greek or Fresh Garlic", "Salt Yogurt (creamier the better)", "1 Tbsp Oregano", "Extra Parmesan", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder", "1/2 Tbsp Black Pepper", "Fresh Parsley", "1/2 Tsp Smoked Paprika", "10g (0.3oz) Parmesan Cheese", "Pinch of Salt", "1 Tsp Cornflour"], "steps": ["Slice the potatoes into thin, even fries. Place them in a large bowl and season with garlic powder, oregano, black pepper, grated parmesan cheese, and cornflour. Lightly spray with cooking spray and toss everything together until the fries are evenly coated.", "Preheat your oven to 220°C (425°F). Spread the fries out in a single layer on a lined baking tray, ensuring they’re not overlapping. Bake for 25–30 minutes, flipping halfway through, until crispy and golden. Alternatively, cook in an air fryer at 220°C for 12–14 minutes, shaking halfway.", "Once the fries are cooked, immediately sprinkle with salt, a bit more parmesan, and some freshly chopped parsley for extra flavour and a pop of colour.", "For the dipping sauce, combine light mayonnaise, fat-free yogurt, crushed or finely minced garlic, paprika, and a pinch of salt in a small bowl. Stir until smooth. Serve the fries hot with the sauce on the side—enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 102"], "canonical_ingredients": ["cheese_parmesan", "cooking_spray", "corn", "flour", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "mayo", "oregano", "paprika", "parsley", "pepper", "potato", "salt", "yogurt"], "tags": ["mediterranean", "italian"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 12, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_low_calorie_crispy_fries", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 103, "name": "Low Calorie Crispy Fries", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 351, "protein": 61.0, "carbs": 11.0, "fat": 7.0}, "ingredients": ["300g (10.6oz) Potatoes, cut into fries Garlic sauce:", "1 Tbsp Smoked Paprika", "80g (2.8oz) Fat Free Yogurt (Greek yogurt works)", "1 Tbsp Black Pepper", "20g (1oz) Light Mayo", "1 Tbsp Garlic Powder", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder", "1 Tbsp Cornstarch or Cornflour (optional)", "1 Tsp Paprika or Chilli Powder", "1/4 Tsp Salt"], "steps": ["Wash the potatoes thoroughly and cut them into thin, even fries. Spread them out on a lined baking tray. Season generously with smoked paprika, black pepper, garlic powder, and a dusting of cornstarch. Toss well to ensure all the fries are evenly coated.", "Preheat your oven to 220°C (430°F). Once heated, bake the fries for 20–23 minutes or until golden and crispy, flipping them halfway through for even browning.", "While the fries are baking, prepare your dipping sauce of choice. Once the fries are out of the oven, sprinkle with salt while still hot and serve immediately with the sauce—enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 103"], "canonical_ingredients": ["chili_powder", "corn", "cornstarch", "flour", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "mayo", "paprika", "pepper", "potato", "salt", "yogurt"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 21, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_golden_yellow_rice", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 104, "name": "Golden Yellow Rice", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 213, "protein": 6.0, "carbs": 44.0, "fat": 2.0}, "ingredients": ["1 Tsp Olive Oil", "1 Tsp Black Pepper", "1/2 Onion, chopped", "1 Tsp Paprika", "1/2 Carrot, chopped", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder", "1/2 Red Bell Pepper, chopped", "1 Tsp Turmeric", "200g (7.1oz) Uncooked Rice, washed", "420ml (14.7oz) Water or Chicken", "1 Tsp Salt Broth (for more flavour)", "Fresh Parsley or Coriander (for garnish)"], "steps": ["Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a pan over medium heat. Add the chopped Bring to a boil then simmer on onions, carrots, and red bell pepper. Sauté for 3–4 minutes until the low heat for another 8 mins till vegetables begin to soften and the onions turn translucent. fully cooked through. Check and mix the rice half way", "Push the vegetables to the sides to make a well in the center of the so it doesn’t stick to the pan. pan. Add the washed, uncooked rice into the well. Season with salt, black pepper, paprika, garlic powder, and turmeric. Stir to evenly You can also make this in a pot coat the rice in the spices and let it toast for 2–3 minutes, allowing the for convenience. flavors to infuse.", "Pour in water or chicken broth, just enough to cover the rice. Stir everything together, then bring the mixture to a light boil. Once boiling, reduce the heat to low, cover the pan, and let it simmer for 8–10 minutes until the rice is fully cooked. Stir gently halfway through to prevent sticking and ensure even cooking.", "Once the rice is tender and the liquid absorbed, fluff it gently. Serve warm with your favorite protein—like grilled chicken or fish—and garnish with fresh parsley or coriander. Enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 104"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bell_pepper", "carrot", "cilantro", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "olive_oil", "onion", "paprika", "parsley", "pepper", "salt"], "tags": ["mediterranean", "indian"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 11, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_spicy_creamy_breakfast_wraps", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 105, "name": "Spicy Creamy Breakfast Wraps", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 300, "protein": 26.0, "carbs": 22.0, "fat": 13.0}, "ingredients": ["6 Boiled Eggs (keep 3 Egg Yolks and 6 whites)", "Low Calorie Tortilla Wraps", "80g (2.8oz) Light Cream Cheese", "Shredded Lettuce", "1-2 Tbsp Sriracha", "15g (0.5oz) Shredded Mozzarella (per wrap)", "1 Red Onion, chopped", "Parsley (for garnish)", "Fresh Parsley", "Sun Dried Tomatoes (optional)", "Salt, Pepper, Chilli Flakes (for seasoning)"], "steps": ["Bring a pot of water to a gentle boil and carefully add 6 eggs. Boil for 8 minutes, then immediately transfer the eggs to a bowl of cold water to cool. Once cooled, peel the eggs and separate the yolks from the whites into two separate bowls.", "Mash the egg yolks until smooth, then add a spoonful of Greek yogurt or light mayo, a squeeze of mustard (optional), salt, pepper, and a pinch of paprika. Mix until it becomes a creamy, well-seasoned base.", "Finely chop the egg whites and add them to the yolk mixture. Stir thoroughly to combine into a cohesive, creamy egg salad.", "Lay out your tortilla wrap of choice. Add a layer of shredded lettuce, a generous spoonful of the egg salad, a sprinkle of grated cheese, and a touch of fresh parsley. Fold the wrap, toast it in a pan on medium heat until golden and warm, then slice and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 105"], "canonical_ingredients": ["cheese_mozzarella", "chili_flakes", "cream_cheese", "eggs", "lettuce", "onion", "parsley", "salt", "sriracha", "tomato", "tortilla", "wrap"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["breakfast", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_crispy_potatoes_scrambled_eggs", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 106, "name": "Crispy Potatoes & Scrambled Eggs", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 451, "protein": 27.0, "carbs": 43.0, "fat": 19.0}, "ingredients": ["250g (8.8oz) Raw Potatoes, cut into little cubes", "Low Fat Spicy Mayo (optional)", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "Chilli Flakes & Parsley (for garnish)", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder Spicy mayo:", "1 Tsp Oregano", "2 Whole Eggs", "Low Fat Mayo", "3 Egg Whites", "Sriracha", "1-2 Tsp Olive Oil", "Paprika"], "steps": ["Start by slicing your potatoes into small, evenly sized cubes. Transfer Microwave the potatoes for 4-5 them to a bowl and season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, and mins before cooking. They come oregano. Microwave the seasoned potatoes for 4–5 minutes until they out soft and this will save you a lot of time! It’s such a great hack. become soft and partially cooked.", "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and add a bit of olive oil or cooking spray. Add the microwaved potatoes and cook for about 4 minutes until they begin to turn golden. Then sprinkle in 1 teaspoon of paprika and continue cooking for another 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until they’re crispy and golden brown.", "While the potatoes are finishing up, prepare your scrambled eggs. Crack your eggs into a bowl, whisk well, then pour into a pan over low heat. Stir gently and continuously for soft, fluffy eggs.", "To serve, plate the crispy potatoes and fluffy eggs together. Drizzle with spicy mayo, season the eggs with salt, pepper, and chili flakes, and garnish with fresh parsley. Enjoy your hearty, flavour-packed breakfast! Return to Table of Contents 106"], "canonical_ingredients": ["chili_flakes", "eggs", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "mayo", "olive_oil", "oregano", "paprika", "parsley", "potato", "salt", "sriracha"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 11, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_cheesecake_french_toast", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 107, "name": "Cheesecake French Toast", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 446, "protein": 35.0, "carbs": 45.0, "fat": 14.0}, "ingredients": ["2 Whole Eggs", "80g (2.8oz) Light Cream Cheese", "2 Egg Whites", "50g (1.7oz) Srawberries, chopped", "1/4 Cup Almond Milk (or any Milk)", "1 Tsp Strawberry Jam (low sugar preferably)", "1 Tsp Vanilla Extract", "1 Tsp Cinnamon", "2 Slices Wholemeal Bread"], "steps": ["In a wide bowl or shallow dish, crack in the whole eggs and egg whites. Add milk, vanilla extract, and a dash of cinnamon. Whisk everything together thoroughly until the mixture is smooth and slightly frothy.", "Dip each slice of bread into the egg mixture, coating both sides evenly without soaking too long. Set the soaked slices aside on a plate, ready to cook.", "In a separate bowl, combine softened cream cheese, finely chopped strawberries, and a spoonful of strawberry jam. Mix until well blended into a creamy, fruity filling.", "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and lightly coat with cooking spray or a bit of olive oil. Cook each slice of soaked bread for about 2 minutes per side, or until golden brown and slightly crispy.", "To assemble, place one slice of the cooked French toast on a plate, spread a layer of the strawberry cream mixture, top with fresh strawberry slices, then place another slice on top. Add more cream, extra berries, and a dusting of powdered sugar. Serve warm and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 107"], "canonical_ingredients": ["almonds", "bread", "cinnamon", "cream_cheese", "eggs", "milk", "strawberry"], "tags": ["mediterranean"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_high_protein_egg_sandwich", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 108, "name": "High Protein Egg Sandwich", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 324, "protein": 26.0, "carbs": 31.0, "fat": 7.5}, "ingredients": ["2 Whole Eggs and 4 Egg Whites", "1/2 Tsp Paprika", "2 Tbsp Low Fat Cream Cheese", "Green Onion or Scallion, chopped", "1/2 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "4 Slices Wholegrain/Wholemeal Bread", "1/2 Tsp Onion Powder", "Lettuce", "Red Chilli Flakes & Parsley (for garnish)"], "steps": ["Begin by boiling your eggs for 8 minutes until hard-boiled. Once done, cool them under cold water, peel carefully, and separate the yolks from the whites.", "In a bowl, place 2 of the yolks and add low-fat cream cheese. Season with salt, pepper, onion powder, paprika, and finely chopped green onion. Mix everything together until smooth and creamy.", "Chop the remaining egg whites into small pieces and fold them into the creamy yolk mixture. Stir until everything is evenly combined.", "Toast 4 slices of wholemeal bread to your preferred crispiness. Assemble each slice with a layer of fresh lettuce, a generous spoonful of the egg mix, and finish with a sprinkle of chilli flakes and chopped parsley. Serve and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 108"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bread", "chili_flakes", "cream_cheese", "eggs", "green_onion", "lettuce", "onion", "onion_powder", "paprika", "parsley", "salt"], "tags": ["mediterranean"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_breakfast_wrap", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 109, "name": "Breakfast Wrap", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 446, "protein": 33.0, "carbs": 28.0, "fat": 21.0}, "ingredients": ["4 Turkey Rashers or Slices", "3 Slices Tomato", "1 Whole Egg", "Salt, Pepper, Garlic Powder (for seasoning)", "1 Wholemeal Wrap", "50g (1.7oz) Avocado, sliced", "Handful Spinach", "Spicy Mayo (mix Sriracha Light Mayo and Lemon Juice)"], "steps": ["Place a non-stick pan over medium heat and add the turkey bacon. Cook until crispy, turning occasionally to ensure even browning.", "Once the bacon is cooked, pour the beaten eggs directly over it in the pan, spreading evenly.", "Reduce the heat to low and immediately place a tortilla wrap on top of the eggs while they’re still wet. Gently press the wrap down so it sticks. Let the eggs cook through completely, then carefully flip the entire wrap using a wide spatula. Toast the underside for 1–2 minutes until lightly golden.", "With the egg side facing out, layer on fresh spinach, tomato slices, a pinch of salt and pepper, sliced avocado, and a drizzle of spicy mayo. Fold the wrap over, remove from the pan, and serve warm. Return to Table of Contents 109"], "canonical_ingredients": ["avocado", "eggs", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "mayo", "salt", "spinach", "tomato", "wrap"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["breakfast", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_breakfast_pizza", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 110, "name": "Breakfast Pizza", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 376, "protein": 30.0, "carbs": 28.0, "fat": 16.0}, "ingredients": ["Low Carb Tortilla Wrap", "1/2 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "2 Whole eggs + 2 Egg Whites (you", "1/2 Tsp Oregano can use all egg whites)", "Red Chilli Flakes", "Handful Cherry Tomatoes", "30g (1.1oz) Low Fat Cheese", "1/2 Bell Pepper", "Spicy Mayo (optional)", "1/2 Red Onion"], "steps": ["Preheat your oven or air fryer to 180°C (350°F). Line a circular baking Macros will vary based on brands dish or pan with baking paper, then gently press a tortilla wrap into the and ingredients you use! dish, shaping it to fit the base and sides like a crust.", "Pour the whisked eggs into the tortilla base. Evenly distribute chopped cherry tomatoes, bell pepper, and red onion over the top. Season with salt, pepper, oregano, and chilli flakes, then sprinkle a generous layer of cheese.", "Bake or air fry for about 10 minutes, or until the eggs are set and the cheese is melted and golden.", "Remove from the oven, let it cool slightly, then slice into portions and serve warm. Enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 110"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bell_pepper", "cherry_tomato", "chili_flakes", "eggs", "mayo", "onion", "oregano", "salt", "tomato", "tortilla", "wrap"], "tags": ["mediterranean"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_pancake_tacos", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 111, "name": "Pancake Tacos", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 186, "protein": 18.0, "carbs": 13.0, "fat": 6.0}, "ingredients": ["50g (1.7oz) Rolled or Old Fashioned Oats", "1 Whole Egg + 3 Egg Whites", "125g (4.4oz) Low Fat Greek Yogurt", "Salt & Pepper (for seasoning)", "1 Whole Egg + 1 Egg White", "3 Pieces Turkey Bacon", "1 Tsp Baking Powder", "10g (0.3oz) Shredded Mozzarella", "Pinch of Salt", "Parsley (for garnish)", "Sriracha"], "steps": ["In a blender cup, combine oats, Greek yogurt, eggs, baking powder, and a pinch of salt. Blend for about 1–2 minutes until the mixture is completely smooth and pourable.", "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat. Pour the pancake batter into the pan in small rounds and cook for 1.5–2 minutes per side, or until golden and cooked through. In the same or a separate pan, scramble your eggs and cook 3 pieces of turkey bacon until crispy.", "Assemble your plate with the pancakes, scrambled eggs, and turkey bacon. Top with low-fat cheese, a drizzle of sriracha, and your favorite seasonings. Enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 111"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bacon", "cheese_mozzarella", "eggs", "oats", "parsley", "salt", "sriracha", "yogurt"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 21, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["pork"]}, {"id": "jalal_blt_sandwich", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 112, "name": "BLT Sandwich", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 490, "protein": 34.0, "carbs": 31.0, "fat": 25.0}, "ingredients": ["4 Slices of Leaner Turkey Bacon (you can use any meat slices like chicken or beef)", "1 Egg + 2-3 Egg Whites (i used a golden yolk egg)", "2 Slices Wholegrain Bread", "1/2 Small Avocado", "Handful of Spinach", "50g (1.7oz) Sriracha or Spicy Mayo", "2 Slices of Tomato Note: You can reduce the fat by using only egg whites", "Salt, Pepper, Chilli Flakes & Garlic and using less or no avocado! Powder (for seasoning)"], "steps": ["Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat and lightly spray with oil. Pour in your whisked egg mixture, then immediately lay two slices of wholemeal bread on top of the uncooked egg. Allow the egg to fully cook and set for a few minutes.", "Use a spatula to gently loosen the edges of the egg from the pan. Slide the spatula underneath and carefully flip the entire egg and bread layer in one motion.", "Once flipped, fold the sides of the cooked egg inward. Layer your fillings on one side: lettuce or greens, sliced tomato, seasonings (salt, pepper, chili flakes, garlic powder), cooked turkey bacon, sliced avocado, and a drizzle of spicy mayo.", "Fold the other slice of bread over the filling to form a sandwich. Toast both sides for a couple more minutes until golden and crispy. Slice and serve warm — enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 112"], "canonical_ingredients": ["avocado", "bacon", "bread", "chili_flakes", "eggs", "garlic", "mayo", "salt", "spinach", "sriracha", "tomato"], "tags": ["asian"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["pork"]}, {"id": "jalal_cream_stuffed_french_toast", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 113, "name": "Cream Stuffed French Toast", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 570, "protein": 48.0, "carbs": 42.0, "fat": 15.0}, "ingredients": ["3 Slices Wholemeal Bread Filling:", "2 Whole Eggs", "1 Tbsp Low Fat Cream Cheese", "1/2 Cup Egg Whites", "1 Tbsp Fat Free Greek Yogurt (vanilla preferably)", "1/4 Cup Almond Milk", "1 Tsp Low Sugar Strawberry Jam", "1 Tsp Vanilla Extract", "1 Tsp Cinnamon"], "steps": ["In a bowl or dish, combine the eggs and egg whites, almond milk, vanilla extract, and a dash of cinnamon. Whisk thoroughly until the mixture is frothy and bubbles form on the surface.", "Dip the slices of bread into the egg mixture, ensuring both sides are lightly soaked. Heat a pan over medium heat and cook each slice for about 2 minutes per side, or until golden brown and cooked through.", "In a small bowl, mix together cream cheese and Greek yogurt until smooth. Add a teaspoon of your favorite jam and gently fold it in to create a swirled effect.", "On a serving plate, start layering by placing a slice of the cooked bread, then spread some of the cream cheese mixture, and top with sliced strawberries. Repeat this layering two more times. Finish with a sprinkle of cinnamon or a drizzle of maple syrup, then enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 113"], "canonical_ingredients": ["almonds", "bread", "cinnamon", "cream_cheese", "eggs", "milk", "strawberry", "sugar", "yogurt"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_loaded_breakfast_eggs", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 114, "name": "Loaded Breakfast Eggs", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 600, "protein": 42.0, "carbs": 34.0, "fat": 24.0}, "ingredients": ["4 Whole Eggs or Egg whites", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "1 White Potato, diced", "1 Tsp Mixed Herbs", "1/2 or 1 Bell Pepper, chopped", "1 Tsp Paprika", "1/2 or 1 White Onion, chopped", "1 Tbsp Olive Oil or Cooking Spray", "1 Red Chilli Pepper, chopped"], "steps": ["Cut the potato into thin chips or fries. Heat a pan over medium-high You can reduce the calories and heat and add olive oil. Once hot, add the potatoes and cook for 5–6 fats by using egg whites indtead minutes, stirring occasionally until they turn crispy. To speed up cooking of whole eggs + using cooking spray instead of olive oil! and promote even crispiness, cover the pan with a lid. Check the potatoes to make", "Add diced onions, bell pepper, and red chili pepper to the pan. Season sure they are fairly cooked everything with mixed herbs and paprika, then cook for another 2–3 before adding the eggs. One tip minutes until the vegetables soften. to make the potatoes crispier,", "Lower the heat and crack in 4 eggs or egg whites evenly over the add paprika when you first cook vegetables. Season again to taste. Cover the pan with a lid and let them the eggs cook through, spreading the egg whites evenly for better, consistent cooking. Serve and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 114"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bell_pepper", "cooking_spray", "eggs", "olive_oil", "onion", "paprika", "potato", "salt"], "tags": ["mediterranean"], "cook_min": 21, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_creamy_scrambled_eggs_on_toast", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 115, "name": "Creamy Scrambled Eggs on Toast", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 425, "protein": 35.0, "carbs": 36.0, "fat": 12.0}, "ingredients": ["2 Whole Eggs + 2 Egg Whites", "1 Tbsp Low Fat Cream Cheese", "Sprinkle of salt and pepper", "2 Slices Wholemeal Bread (toasted)", "Chilli Flakes (for seasoning)", "Chives (for seasoning)", "Spicy Honey or regular Honey"], "steps": ["Crack your eggs into a bowl and whisk them thoroughly until well combined. Pour the eggs into a non-stick pan over low heat and begin scrambling, stirring gently until they are about 80% cooked but still slightly soft.", "Add dollops of cream cheese to the eggs and slowly fold it in, allowing it to melt and create a creamy texture. Season with salt and pepper to taste.", "Toast your wholemeal bread, then spoon the creamy scrambled eggs on top. Sprinkle with chili flakes, chopped chives, and drizzle some spicy honey over everything. You’re ready to enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 115"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bread", "chili_flakes", "cream_cheese", "eggs", "honey", "salt"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 21, "prep_min": 8, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_tiramisu_pancakes", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 116, "name": "Tiramisu Pancakes", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 459, "protein": 43.0, "carbs": 55.0, "fat": 7.0}, "ingredients": ["60g (2.1oz) Oats Filling:", "1 Scoop Vanilla Protein Powder", "1 Tsp Instant Coffee (mixed in water)", "1/2 Tsp Baking Powder", "150g (5.3oz) Fat Free Vanilla Greek Yogurt (any", "Pinch of Baking Soda yogurt works with some vanilla extract)", "1 Tbsp Maple Syrup", "Sprinkle of Cocoa Powder", "1 Coffee Shot (1 Tsp Instant Coffee mixed with 2 Tbsp Almond Milk)", "100ml (3.5oz) Almond Milk", "Cooking Spray"], "steps": ["Add all your ingredients to a blender cup, starting with the dry ingredients followed by the wet ones. Blend for 1–2 minutes until the batter is completely smooth and lump-free.", "Heat a non-stick pan over medium-low heat and lightly spray with oil. Pour in 1/4 cup of the pancake batter and cook for about 2 minutes until bubbles form and the edges are set. Flip and cook for another minute. Repeat with the remaining batter to make 4 pancakes.", "Once all pancakes are done, stack them layer by layer—starting with a pancake, then a drizzle of coffee, followed by a spoonful of yogurt. Repeat for all layers. On the final pancake, dust with cocoa powder and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 116"], "canonical_ingredients": ["almonds", "cooking_spray", "milk", "oats", "yogurt"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 21, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_fluffy_thicc_pancakes", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 117, "name": "Fluffy Thicc Pancakes", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 431, "protein": 34.0, "carbs": 46.0, "fat": 10.0}, "ingredients": ["60g (2.1oz) Rolled or Old Fashioned Oats", "1 Whole Egg + 2 Egg Whites", "125g (4.4oz) Low Fat Vanilla Greek Yogurt (High Protein)", "1 Tsp Vanilla Extract", "1 Tsp Baking Powder"], "steps": ["Add all your ingredients to a blender and blend for 45 seconds to 1 minute until smooth and well combined. Let the batter sit for a few minutes to thicken slightly and allow the ingredients to settle.", "Heat a non-stick pan over low heat and lightly spray with oil if needed. Pour in about 1/3 or 1/4 cup of the batter per pancake. Cook each one for 1 to 1.5 minutes per side, flipping once the edges are set and bubbles appear on the surface.", "Stack the pancakes on a plate and top with fresh blueberries, sliced strawberries, and a drizzle of sugar- free syrup. Serve and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 117"], "canonical_ingredients": ["eggs", "oats", "yogurt"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 21, "prep_min": 7, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_high_protein_quesadilla", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 118, "name": "High Protein Quesadilla", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 450, "protein": 39.0, "carbs": 32.0, "fat": 16.0}, "ingredients": ["4 Slices Turkey Bacon", "1 Whole Egg", "30g (1.1oz) Low Fat Mozzarella", "3 Egg Whites", "Sriracha", "1 Low Calorie Tortilla", "Pinch of Salt & Pepper", "Handful of Spinach", "1/2 Tsp Mixed Herbs", "3 Slices Tomato (season with Salt and Pepper) Note: you can use any low calorie tortilla or low fat cheese"], "steps": ["Heat a non-stick pan over low heat and lightly spray with oil. Pour in your Make sure you toast the tortilla whisked eggs and let them begin to set for about 1 minute. Then gently properly to get a nice hard crust. press a tortilla onto the eggs and flip it so the tortilla sits underneath and the egg is on top.", "Let the egg cook for another 3–4 minutes until fully set. Use a spatula to gently loosen the edges and slide underneath the tortilla to ensure it’s not sticking. Carefully flip it over so the tortilla side is now on the pan.", "On one half of the tortilla, layer fresh spinach, tomato slices, cooked turkey bacon, shredded cheese, a drizzle of sriracha, and any desired seasoning.", "Fold the other half of the tortilla over to close it. If it’s not golden and crisp enough, toast each side for another minute or two. Serve warm and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 118"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bacon", "cheese_mozzarella", "eggs", "salt", "spinach", "sriracha", "tomato", "tortilla"], "tags": ["asian"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["pork"]}, {"id": "jalal_loaded_omelette_low_carb", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 119, "name": "Loaded Omelette (Low carb)", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 380, "protein": 46.0, "carbs": 5.0, "fat": 14.0}, "ingredients": ["2 Whole Eggs", "Pinch of Salt & Pepper", "2-3 Egg Whites", "Pinch of Paprika", "1/4 Cup (2oz) Almond or Low Fat Milk", "Pinch of Garlic Powder", "4 Slices Turkey Bacon", "Handful of Spinach", "Handful Cherry Tomatoes", "Low Fat Cream Cheese"], "steps": ["Crack the eggs into a bowl, add a splash of almond or low fat milk, and whisk until fully combined and slightly frothy.", "In a pan over medium heat, cook the turkey slices until crispy, then set aside on a plate.", "Using the same pan, add halved cherry tomatoes and season with salt, pepper, paprika, and garlic powder. Cook for about 2 minutes, then add spinach and cover until it wilts.", "Add the cooked veggies and turkey to the egg mixture, gently stirring to combine.", "Pour the egg mixture back into the pan over low heat. Add a few small dollops of cream cheese and lightly season the top. Cook gently until set, or finish under the grill for 2 minutes until lightly golden. Serve and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 119"], "canonical_ingredients": ["almonds", "bacon", "cherry_tomato", "cream_cheese", "eggs", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "milk", "paprika", "salt", "spinach", "tomato"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["pork"]}, {"id": "jalal_breakfast_pizza_2", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 120, "name": "Breakfast Pizza", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 500, "protein": 36.0, "carbs": 32.0, "fat": 22.0}, "ingredients": ["1 Wholemeal or Plain Tortilla", "Handful of Spinach, Chopped", "4 Eggs or Egg Whites", "Pinch of Salt, Pepper and Paprika (For Seasoning)", "1 Chilli Pepper, Chopped", "15g (0.5oz) Mozzarella Cheese", "1/2 Tomato, Chopped"], "steps": ["Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F) and place a tortilla wrap into a Make sure you toast the tortilla small baking dish or oven-safe bowl, pressing it in so the edges form a properly to get a nice hard crust. raised crust.", "Crack a couple of eggs directly into the center of the wrap.", "Add chopped chilli pepper, diced tomato, a handful of spinach, and shredded mozzarella on top.", "Season with salt, pepper, and any herbs you like.", "Bake in the oven for about 10 minutes, or until the eggs are set and the edges of the tortilla are golden. Remove and enjoy immediately! Return to Table of Contents 120"], "canonical_ingredients": ["cheese_mozzarella", "eggs", "paprika", "pepper", "salt", "spinach", "tomato", "tortilla"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 8, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_cheesecake_overnight_oats", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 121, "name": "Cheesecake Overnight Oats", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 395, "protein": 43.0, "carbs": 42.0, "fat": 8.0}, "ingredients": ["35g (1.2oz) Rolled or Old Fashioned Oats For the layers:", "1 Scoop (30g, 1,1oz) Protein Powder (Vanilla Flavoured)", "30g (1.1oz) Cream Cheese", "30-40g (1.4oz) Low Fat Cream Cheese", "30g (1.1oz) Yogurt", "30g (1.1oz) Fat Free Greek Yogurt (Makes it extra creamy)", "15g (0.5oz) Low Sugar Strawberry Jam", "15g (0.5oz) Granola", "20-30ml (1.1oz) Almond or Low Fat Milk Toppings:", "Fresh Ftrawberries", "Granola For Extra Crunch"], "steps": ["In a bowl, combine oats, protein powder, cream cheese, Greek yogurt, strawberry jam, and milk. Mix until smooth and fully combined.", "Grab a glass or jar and start layering: begin with granola, then yogurt, followed by jam, cheesecake mixture, more jam, another layer of cheesecake mix, and finish with a spoonful of yogurt.", "Add your favorite toppings like fresh fruit, extra granola, or a drizzle of jam.", "You can enjoy it right away for a quick treat, or refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight for a creamier texture.", "Serve chilled and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 121"], "canonical_ingredients": ["almonds", "cream_cheese", "milk", "oats", "strawberry", "sugar", "yogurt"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 35, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_original_overnight_oats", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 122, "name": "Original Overnight Oats", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 400, "protein": 38.0, "carbs": 48.0, "fat": 6.0}, "ingredients": ["1/2 Cup (4oz) Old Fashioned or Rolled Oats", "1 Scoop Protein Powder", "1/2 Cup (4oz)