book V2", "source_page": 125, "name": "Eggs on Toast MY WAY", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 450, "protein": 24.0, "carbs": 32.0, "fat": 24.0}, "ingredients": ["1 Tsp Olive Oil or Cooking Spray", "2 Slices Wholemeal Bread", "2 Whole Eggs", "30g (1.1oz) Low fat Cream Cheese", "2 Egg White (Optional For More Protein)", "Handful Spinach", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "1/2 Avocado", "1/2 Tsp Red Chilli Flakes", "Sriracha", "1/2 Tsp Paprika"], "steps": ["Heat a pan over medium heat, spray lightly with oil, and crack in your Reduce fat by using egg whites eggs. Season with salt, pepper, chilli flakes, and paprika, then cook and less avocado. until done to your liking.", "Toast your bread and place it on a plate. Spread a layer of cream cheese on the toast, then add fresh spinach, avocado slices, and a drizzle of sriracha.", "Place the cooked eggs on top of everything.", "It’s ready to enjoy, simple, hearty, and full of flavour! Return to Table of Contents 125"], "canonical_ingredients": ["avocado", "bread", "chili_flakes", "cooking_spray", "cream_cheese", "eggs", "olive_oil", "paprika", "salt", "spinach", "sriracha"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_hi_pro_pancakes", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 126, "name": "Hi-Pro Pancakes", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 100, "protein": 8.0, "carbs": 8.0, "fat": 4.0}, "ingredients": ["1 Cup (8oz) Rolled Oats Toppings:", "1 Cup (8oz) Zero Fat Greek Yogurt", "Mixed Merries", "1/4 Cup (2oz) Coconut Flour", "Low Sugar Maple Syrup", "1 Scoop Protein Powder (Vanilla Flavoured)", "2 Whole Eggs", "1 Tsp Baking Powder", "1 Tsp Baking Soda", "1/4 Cup (2oz) Almond Milk", "1 Tsp Vanilla Extract"], "steps": ["Add all ingredients to a blender in the listed order and blend until the mixture is completely smooth with no lumps.", "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat. Pour in about 1/4 cup of the pancake batter.", "Cook for around 2 minutes or until the edges are set and the bottom is golden, then flip and cook the other side.", "Stack the cooked pancakes on a plate. Top with fresh berries and a drizzle of low-sugar maple syrup—ready to enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 126"], "canonical_ingredients": ["almonds", "eggs", "flour", "milk", "oats", "sugar", "yogurt"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_french_toast_muffins", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 127, "name": "French Toast Muffins", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 103, "protein": 10.0, "carbs": 12.0, "fat": 1.0}, "ingredients": ["8 Slices Low Calorie Bread", "1 Tsp Vanilla Extract", "1 Cup (8oz) Egg Whites", "1 Tsp Cinnamon", "1 Cup (8oz) Low Fat or Almond Milk", "Apple Sauce", "1 Scoop Protein Powder"], "steps": ["In a large bowl, whisk together egg whites, almond milk, protein powder, vanilla extract, and cinnamon until smooth and bubbly. Cut 8 slices of low-calorie bread into cubes, then gently fold them into the mixture and let soak for a few minutes.", "Preheat the oven to 180°C (350°F) and lightly grease a muffin tray with cooking spray.", "Divide the soaked bread mixture evenly into the muffin tray cups, topping each with a teaspoon of apple sauce.", "Bake for 20–25 minutes until golden and set. Let cool slightly, then enjoy warm with maple syrup if you like! Return to Table of Contents 127"], "canonical_ingredients": ["almonds", "apple", "bread", "cinnamon", "eggs", "milk"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 8, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_breakfast_eggs_potato", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 128, "name": "Breakfast Eggs & Potato", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 430, "protein": 27.0, "carbs": 36.0, "fat": 15.0}, "ingredients": ["1 Medium Potato, Diced", "1 Tomato, Chopped", "Pinch of Salt & Pepper", "Eggs (I Did 3 Eggs + 1 Egg White)", "Paprika", "Handful Spinach", "1/2 Onion, Chopped", "Siracha", "1/2 Bell Pepper, Chopped"], "steps": ["Dice the potatoes into small pieces and chop all your vegetables. Heat You can reduce cals by just a pan with cooking spray, add the potatoes, season with salt, pepper, using egg whites. and paprika, then cook for about 10 minutes. Spray more oil if needed and cover the pan to speed up cooking.", "Push the potatoes to one side of the pan, add the chopped onion and bell pepper, season again, and cook for 2 minutes. Then mix everything together and add the chopped tomatoes.", "Make a well in the center of the pan and pour in the eggs. Stir continuously over medium heat until the eggs begin to scramble.", "Mix the eggs with the veggies, add a handful of chopped spinach, cook briefly until wilted, then serve hot. Don’t forget to add sriracha for that extra kick! Enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 128"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bell_pepper", "eggs", "onion", "paprika", "potato", "salt", "spinach", "tomato"], "tags": ["asian"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_breakfast_scrambled_wrap", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 129, "name": "Breakfast Scrambled Wrap", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 500, "protein": 25.0, "carbs": 35.0, "fat": 18.0}, "ingredients": ["2-3 Eggs", "Handful Spinach, Chopped 1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "1 Low Calorie Tortilla Wrap", "1 Tsp Garlic Powder", "1 Tsp Olive Oil", "1 Tsp Paprika", "1/2 Onion, Chopped", "15g (0.5oz) Shredded Mozzarella", "1/2 Bell Pepper, Chopped", "15g (0.5oz) Sriracha", "1/2 Avocado, Sliced"], "steps": ["Dice the onion, bell pepper, and spinach. Heat olive oil in a pan over You can reduce fat by using just medium heat, then add the onion and bell pepper. Season with salt, egg whites. pepper, garlic powder, and paprika, and cook for 2 minutes.", "Add the spinach, stir to combine, then push all the veggies to one side of the pan.", "Pour the eggs into the empty side and stir continuously until cooked through. Mix the eggs with the veggies.", "Place a low-calorie tortilla on a plate, add the egg and veggie mixture in the center, top with mozzarella, sriracha, and sliced avocado. Roll it up and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 129"], "canonical_ingredients": ["avocado", "bell_pepper", "cheese_mozzarella", "eggs", "garlic", "garlic_powder", "olive_oil", "onion", "paprika", "salt", "spinach", "sriracha", "tortilla", "wrap"], "tags": ["asian", "mediterranean"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["breakfast", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_loaded_sandwich", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 130, "name": "Loaded Sandwich", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 500, "protein": 40.0, "carbs": 32.0, "fat": 17.0}, "ingredients": ["2-3 Eggs (Egg Whites For Low Fat)", "3 Turkey Slices", "2 Slices Wholemeal Bread", "1 Red Bell Pepper, Chopped", "Cooking Spray", "Mixed Greens", "1 Tsp Salt & Pepper", "Sriracha", "1 Tsp Mixed Herbs", "Low Fat Cheese", "1 Tsp Paprika"], "steps": ["Spray oil on a non-stick pan over low heat. Crack the eggs into the pan Lower calories/fat with egg and immediately place two slices of bread on top. whites.", "Cook until the eggs are almost set, then carefully flip the bread and Calories & Macros will vary based on ingredients you use! eggs together using a wide spatula.", "Fold the sides of the bread inward, season with salt, pepper, and paprika. Layer turkey slices, bell pepper, mixed greens, sriracha, and low-fat cheese on top.", "Fold the top slice of bread over, then toast both sides for a few minutes until crispy. Serve and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 130"], "canonical_ingredients": ["bell_pepper", "bread", "cooking_spray", "eggs", "paprika", "salt", "sriracha"], "tags": ["asian"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 10, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_sweet_potato_pancakes", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 131, "name": "Sweet Potato Pancakes", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 520, "protein": 60.0, "carbs": 50.0, "fat": 8.0}, "ingredients": ["2 Medium Sweet Potatoes Toppings (Choose any):", "1 Cup (8oz) Egg Whites", "Maple Syrup (Low Sugar)", "1 Tsp Vanilla Extract", "1 Tsp Pink or Sea Salt", "1 Tsp Cinnamon", "1-2 Scoops Protein Powder (Optional)", "Cooking Spray Oil"], "steps": ["Wash the sweet potatoes and pierce them with a fork. Microwave for about 8 minutes until soft, then peel and transfer to a bowl.", "Add egg whites, vanilla extract, cinnamon, and protein powder. Mix until the batter is smooth and well combined.", "Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat, spray with oil, and pour in about 1/4 cup of the batter per pancake. Cook for 2 minutes on each side until golden. You should get around 7 pancakes.", "Stack the pancakes on a plate and top with your favorite toppings—low-sugar maple syrup works great. Enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 131"], "canonical_ingredients": ["cinnamon", "cooking_spray", "eggs", "potato", "salt", "sweet_potato"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 28, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_bangin_protein_smoothie", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 137, "name": "Bangin’ Protein Smoothie", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 500, "protein": 34.0, "carbs": 55.0, "fat": 11.0}, "ingredients": ["1 Frozen Banana", "1 Handful Frozen Strawberries (Plus Extra to Serve)", "2 Dates", "60ml (2.1oz) Almond Milk", "1 Tbsp Greek Yogurt", "1 Tbsp Peaut or Almond Butter", "1 Scoop Protein Powder (Vanilla Flavoured)"], "steps": ["Add all the ingredients to a blender, saving a couple of fresh strawberries for garnish. Blend on high speed until the mixture is completely smooth and thick.", "Pour the smoothie into a glass, top with the reserved strawberries (sliced if you like), and enjoy it fresh and chilled! Return to Table of Contents 137"], "canonical_ingredients": ["almonds", "banana", "butter", "milk", "strawberry", "yogurt"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 14, "prep_min": 8, "meal_types": ["breakfast"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_grenadine_summer_refresher", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 138, "name": "Grenadine Summer Refresher", "servings": 4, "macros": null, "ingredients": ["1 Tbsp Grenadine Syrup", "Diced Strawberries", "1 Lime, Juiced (+2/3 Slices for Later)", "Sparkling Water", "Big Handful of Ice Cubes"], "steps": ["In a large glass or mason jar, add a generous amount of ice cubes. Layer in some sliced strawberries, a splash of grenadine syrup, freshly squeezed lime juice, and a few thin slices of lime for extra flavor.", "Pour in sparkling or until the glass is full. Stir gently with a straw or spoon to mix everything together. Refreshing and ready to drink! Return to Table of Contents 138"], "canonical_ingredients": ["strawberry"], "tags": ["mexican"], "cook_min": 14, "prep_min": 7, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_snickers_shake", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 139, "name": "Snickers Shake", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 500, "protein": 33.0, "carbs": 55.0, "fat": 20.0}, "ingredients": ["1 Frozen Banana (100g, 3.5oz) Toppings:", "2 Dates (Soft Dates)", "Sugar Free Chocolate Syrup or", "1 Scoop Chocolate Protein Powder Melted Dark Chocolate", "2 Tbsp Crunchy Peanut Butter", "Crushed Peanuts", "1/2 Tbsp Unsweetened Cocoa Powder", "1 Cup (8oz) Almond Milk", "Handful Ice Cubes"], "steps": ["Add all your ingredients to a blender one at a time, being careful not to overfill it — the mixture will expand slightly as it blends. Secure the lid and blend on high speed for at least 30 seconds until smooth and creamy.", "Pour into a glass, drizzle with sugar-free chocolate syrup, and finish with a sprinkle of crushed peanuts on top. Serve immediately and enjoy! Return to Table of Contents 139"], "canonical_ingredients": ["almonds", "banana", "butter", "milk", "peanut_butter", "sugar"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 14, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_soft_fudgy_choc_cookies", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 140, "name": "Soft & Fudgy Choc Cookies", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 108, "protein": 6.0, "carbs": 17.0, "fat": 2.0}, "ingredients": ["80g (2.8oz) Rolled Oats, Blended", "125g (4.4oz) Unsweetened Applesauce", "1 Scoop Protein Powder", "30g, (1.1oz) Honey or Sugar Free", "1 Tsp Baking Powder (Optional) Syrup (For Lower Calories)", "1/2 Tsp Salt", "15g (0.5oz) Dark Chocolate Chips (Low Sugar)", "1 Tbsp Cocoa Powder (Unsweetened)"], "steps": ["In a mixing bowl, combine blended oats, protein powder, cocoa You can reduce calories and powder, baking powder, applesauce, and honey or sugar-free carbs by using sugar free syrup syrup. Stir until the mixture is smooth, then fold in dark chocolate [Calories: 95 per cookie - chips. Macros: 14g carbs / 6g protein /", "Line a baking tray with parchment paper and spoon the mixture into 2g fat] 6 equal portions. Shape into cookies and, if desired, press in extra chocolate chips and sprinkle a little flaky salt on top.", "Bake in a preheated oven at 180°C (350°F) for about 7 minutes. Once baked, transfer to a wire rack and let them cool for 5 minutes. Enjoy with a cold glass of milk! Return to Table of Contents 140"], "canonical_ingredients": ["apple", "honey", "oats", "salt", "sugar"], "tags": ["american"], "cook_min": 21, "prep_min": 9, "meal_types": ["dinner", "lunch"], "proteins": ["other"]}, {"id": "jalal_protein_ice_cream", "source": "Jalal's Cookbook V2", "source_page": 141, "name": "Protein Ice Cream", "servings": 4, "macros": {"calories": 450, "protein": 40.0, "carbs": 45.0, "fat": 11.0}, "ingredients": ["1 Cup (8oz) Frozen Mango", "1 Cup (8oz) Frozen Strawberries", "1 Cup (8oz) Low Fat Greek Yogurt", "1-2 Scoops Vanilla Protein Powder (Optional)"], "steps": ["